{
  "texts": [
    "The output of the LLM is finally processed by the Activity Label Extraction module to obtain the most likely activity performed by the subject.ADL-LLM works in two different modalities:• Zero-Shot, where no labeled data is available • Few-Shot, where a small labeled dataset is available Indeed, in certain circumstances, it may be possible to collect a small dataset of sensor data windows labeled with the corresponding ADL.",
    "For instance, when the sensing infrastructure is physically installed in the home, the technicians may ask the subject to perform a limited number of activities (as a sort of \"system calibration\" phase).",
    "The data associated with these activities is manually labeled and stored in the Pool of Examples.",
    "In few-shot ADL-LLM, when processing a window, the System Prompt is enriched by the Semantic-based Example Selection module, which picks from this pool the samples that are the most \"semantically\" similar to the textual representation of currently processed window.",
    "The selected samples have the role of further guiding the LLM on the ADLs recognition task."
  ]
}